The number of abducted students of Federal College of Forestry Mechanisation Kaduna has risen to 39, Kaduna State Government has confirmed. The government said 23 females and 16 males were unaccounted for after the incident. Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs, Mr Samuel Aruwan, gave the update in a statement on Friday evening. According to him: “The number of missing students is now confirmed to be 39, comprising 23 females and 16 males. “The Kaduna State Government is maintaining close communication with the management of the College as efforts are sustained by security agencies towards the tracking of the missing students. “Citizens will continue to be informed of further developments.”